"body":"Ashbel Stiles inherited the family mansion and a very comfortable property from his father in North Haven Connecticut. But in an evil hour he endorsed for a friend and lost his all. Soon after he removed to Windsor Connecticut, and thence to Norwich Massachusetts — now Huntington — near his daughter Ruth Stiles Ellis."},{"category":"death","header":"Hannah died Norwich one month before Ashbel did","body":"After fifty-one years of marriage, Ashbel and his cousin-wife Hannah Stiles both died at Norwich (now Huntington) Massachusetts in autumn 1810 — both at age seventy-five. Hannah went first in September; Ashbel followed in October, approximately one month later.","number":100},{"category":"death","header":"Son thrown from a horse, killed in Jamaica","body":"His son Benjamin Stiles died at Jamaica in the West Indies from injuries sustained being thrown from a horse. The Stiles Family in America entry 230 records the death without further circumstance — a son lost an ocean from home to a single fall.","number":101},{"category":"military","header":"Horse Neck garrison 1781 after financial ruin","body":"Forty-six at enlistment, he came to Revolutionary militia service well after most of his cohort. Financial ruin from endorsing for a friend had already emptied the family mansion he had inherited from his father.","number":102}],"slug":"ashbel-stiles-1735"},"I00160":{"id":"I00160","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1735,"month":9,"day":11},"death":{"year":1810,"month":9,"city":"Norwich (Huntington)","state":"Massachusetts"},"parents":{"mother_research_notes":"Mary Phelps Stiles","father_research_notes":"Lt. Samuel Stiles of Windsor CT"},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"H00241","children_ids":["H00460","H00461","H00462","H00463","H00464","H00465"],"marria